Rescuers searched through debris today

He said officials expected the numbers to climb.
The quake, centered almost on the India-Nepal border, registered 6.5 on the Richter scale.
Wooden houses were not affected, he said.
Many people were given shelter in schools, guesthouses and public buildings, "but most of the people do not want to leave their homes," Shahi said.
Parts of northern Bangladesh and the capital, Dhaka, also felt the tremor.
Officials said at least 45 people died, but it was not known whether the deaths were due to floods or collapsing houses.
